FBIS4-30841 "dreeu105_i_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Launch Day-Long Attacks on Gradacac Serbs Launch Day-Long Attacks on Gradacac AU3105194094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 31 May 94 AU3105194094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by unidentified correspondent from the Information Center of the 107th Chivalrous Motorized Brigade of Gradacac] [Excerpt] Attacks on the free territory of Gradacac have lasted all day, since early this morning. The projectiles from all types of weapons are showering the positions of our fighters and the central part of the free territory. [Unidentified correspondent] Three tanks and numerous mortars, guns, howitzers from all the well-known chetnik strongholds took part in the attack today. After two infantry attacks had been successfully repelled, with the enemy suffering major losses, artillery continued to attack the town and the entire front. These attacks are mainly indiscriminate, nervous, and without a particular aim. Stunned by yet another defeat, the Serbo-fascists have been pounding the town all afternoon. [passage omitted]
